      "settings": {
        "checksum": "3fc247ad71bcea7a7b35d84210162fb965dee90fa587b5889e4c2423d5e17e85_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg-INp_hs_3_text": "<p><span style=\"color:rgba(5,23,35,0.5);\"><s>$69.99</s></span></p>",
        "gg-VWowYW6Y_text": "<p>Save 64%</p>",
        "gg-s1U-a7ON_text": "<p>My parents divorced when I was 26. My dad was 51.</p><p><br>At first, he said he was fine being alone. \"I'm focusing on myself,\" he'd tell me. But I could see it in his eyes at family dinners—especially when my sister brought her husband, or when I talked about my wife.</p><p><br>He was lonely. Deeply lonely.</p><p><br>After about two years, he finally admitted he wanted to start dating again. I was thrilled for him.</p><p><br>But then I watched something painful happen.</p><p><br>He'd get ready for a date—nice shirt, cologne, the works—and then he'd catch his reflection in the hallway mirror. His shoulders would drop. He'd touch his neck. Adjust his collar to hide something.</p><p><br>And I'd watch his whole energy shift.</p><p><br>He'd come home from those dates and say things like:</p>",
        "gg01Q_AI12e_text": "<p>By week four, he started noticing changes in the mirror.</p><p><br>The deep lines around his eyes looked softer. Not gone—but less pronounced. Like someone had turned down the contrast.</p><p><br>His skin had a healthier tone to it. Less grey, less dull. More... <i>alive.</i></p><p><br>\"I don't look as tired,\" he said. \"Even when I am tired.\"</p>",
        "gg04un1EaV4_text": "<p>I'm sharing this because I wish someone had told my dad sooner. This is for:</p>",
        "gg07622qCfv_text": "<p>2. Vitamin C from Sicilian Oranges</p>",
        "gg0uL7FEVbi_childItem_0": "<p>Skin so dry it cracks</p>",
        "gg11czd5Oxv_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Drugstore moisturizers</strong> — They hydrate the surface but don't rebuild collagen. You'll have soft, well-moisturized wrinkles.</p>",
        "gg11czd5Oxv_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Beef tallow</strong> — It's occlusive (sits on top of your skin), goes rancid, clogs pores, and does nothing to stimulate collagen production. It's passive when you need active.</p>",
        "gg11czd5Oxv_childItem_2": "<p><strong>Harsh Retinol products</strong> — They work in theory, but the irritation is so bad most men quit before seeing results. Looking like a peeling tomato for 6 weeks isn't worth it.</p>",
        "gg11czd5Oxv_childItem_3": "<p><strong>\"Men's skincare systems\" with 4-5 products</strong> — Overcomplicated, overpriced, and most are just repackaged moisturizers. They're selling you a routine, not results.</p>",
        "gg11czd5Oxv_childItem_4": "<p><strong>Expensive procedures (Botox, fillers)</strong> — They can work, but you&#039;re looking at $500-2,000+ every few months. Plus the \"frozen face\" look. Plus the needles. Plus explaining to everyone why you suddenly look different.</p>",
        "gg24R6sks6a_text": "<p>I'd been searching for an Italian formulation that combined all three elements—Retinyl Palmitate, Vitamin C, and Hyaluronic Acid—in the right concentrations.</p><p><br>Most American brands had one or two of these ingredients, but buried so far down the ingredient list they were basically useless. Just there for the label.</p><p><br>Then I came across a night cream that had been quietly dominating the Italian market for years: <strong>Omnis Uomo.</strong></p><p><br>Over 72,000 Italian men were already using it. Pharmacists across Italy were recommending it as their #1 anti-aging solution for men over 40.</p><p><br>And when I looked at the formulation, I understood why:</p>",
        "gg4p5Dk1QtN_childItem_0": "<p>Peeling</p>",
        "gg5LWbzMBff_text": "<p>You've probably heard of Retinol. It's the gold standard for anti-aging. Dermatologists have been recommending it for decades.</p><p><br>There's just one problem:</p><p><br><strong>Regular Retinol is brutal on your skin.</strong></p><p><br>It works by forcing rapid cell turnover—which sounds great in theory. But in practice? Most men who try it experience what's called \"the purge\":</p>",
        "gg5wRRfSd6B_text": "But here's what the research revealed:",
        "gg8sM3bmz8l_text": "<p>Try it for 60 days. That's enough time to get through the full transformation timeline—the initial hydration in weeks 1-2, and the real structural rebuilding in weeks 6-8.</p><p><br>In the worst case scenario, you're not thrilled with the results—and you get every penny back. Omnis has a 60-day money-back guarantee. No hassles, no hoops to jump through.</p><p><br>In the <i>likely</i> scenario? You start seeing what 72,000+ Italian men have already discovered. Firmer skin. Softer wrinkles. A jawline that looks like it belongs to you again. And that quiet confidence that comes from your outside finally matching your inside.</p><p><br><strong>Risk: $0 (with the guarantee) Potential upside: Looking and feeling like yourself again</strong></p>",
        "ggAHDvWpV4s_text": "<p>It works while you sleep—so there's nothing to \"remember.\"</p>",
        "ggAdiuoVHse_text": "<p>The Italian Formulation Trusted by 72,000+ Men</p>",
        "ggAjO20MpJj_text": "<p>\"I think it's actually doing something.\"</p>",
        "ggAmJLtg0Zt_text": "Here's what I wish someone had asked my dad eight years ago:",
        "ggAvlCP674P_text": "<p><i>\"She was nice, but I could tell she wasn't interested.\"</i></p><p><br><i>\"I don't think I'm what women are looking for anymore.\"</i></p><p><br><i>\"Maybe I'm just too old for this.\"</i></p>",
        "ggC5YZ8qOM-_text": "<p>There's a <i>different</i> form of Vitamin A called <strong>Retinyl Palmitate.</strong></p><p><br>Think of it as Retinol's sophisticated Italian cousin.</p><p><br>Here's how it works:</p><p><br>When you apply Retinyl Palmitate to your skin, it doesn't attack your skin cells directly like regular Retinol does.</p><p><br>Instead, it absorbs slowly and converts into Retinoic Acid <i>inside</i> your skin through a gentle, two-step process.</p><p><br><strong>Same collagen-building benefits. None of the burning, peeling, or redness.</strong></p><p><br>It's why I started calling it the \"Gentleman's Retinol\"—because it works without making you look like you stuck your face in a furnace.</p>",
        "ggCNYyuVOIk_text": "<p>Because here's what I learned watching my dad struggle for almost a decade:</p><p><br><strong>The problem was never his personality. It was never his sense of humor or his stories or his kind heart.</strong></p><p><br>The problem was that every time he looked in the mirror before a date, he saw someone he didn't recognize. And that uncertainty showed.</p>",
        "ggDMwj9KFpx_text": "If you're ready to try what worked for my dad:",
        "ggEXXyMkBhU_text": "So here's the decision in front of you:",
        "ggEdF6KOTi9_text": "<p>Plus, it was specifically formulated for men's skin—which is thicker and oilier than women's, so it needs different concentrations.</p><p><br>And here's what caught my attention:</p><p><br><strong>It was a night cream. One step. Apply before bed, let it work while you sleep.</strong></p><p><br>No complicated routines. No morning serums and evening toners and weekly masks. Just one application at night.</p><p><br>I knew my dad would actually stick with that.</p>",
        "ggEvsHTpE1o_text": "<p><i>\"What is it costing you to feel this way about yourself?\"</i></p><p><br>Not in dollars. In <i>life.</i></p><p><br>How many dates has he cut short because he couldn't stop thinking about his neck?</p><p><br>How many times did he stay home instead of putting himself out there?</p><p><br>How many years did he spend alone—not because he couldn't find someone, but because he didn't feel like he <i>deserved</i> to?</p><p><br>I can't get those years back for my dad.</p><p><br>But I'm grateful he finally found something that let him feel like himself again. That let him walk into a room without that voice in his head telling him everyone's noticing how old he looks.</p><p><br><strong>He deserved to feel confident. So do you.</strong></p>",
        "ggFLFc12zPF_text": "<p>I'm not going to pretend I know your situation. Maybe you're recently divorced like my dad was. Maybe you're happily married but tired of looking tired. Maybe you just want to look in the mirror and see the guy you still feel like inside.</p><p><br>Whatever brought you here, you've got two options:</p>",
        "ggG1v6D0VCL_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Retinyl Palmitate (Gentle Vitamin A) </strong>— Restarts collagen production without the burning, peeling, or redness of harsh retinol</p>",
        "ggG1v6D0VCL_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Vitamin C derived from Sicilian oranges</strong>—stabilized so it doesn't oxidize before it works</p>",
        "ggG1v6D0VCL_childItem_2": "<p><strong>Hyaluronic Acid</strong> for moisture retention and collagen protection</p>",
        "ggG1v6D0VCL_childItem_3": "<p><strong>Cold-pressed Tuscan olive oil</strong> for antioxidant protection</p>",
        "ggG1v6D0VCL_childItem_4": "<p><strong>Night-only application</strong> — One step, 30 seconds, works while you sleep</p>",
        "ggG1v6D0VCL_childItem_5": "<p><strong>Made in Italy</strong> 🇮🇹 — Formulated under strict Italian pharmaceutical regulations</p>",
        "ggG1v6D0VCL_childItem_6": "<p><strong>Approved by Italian Pharmacists</strong> — The #1 recommendation for men over 40 in Italian pharmacies</p>",
        "ggG2lm4gsWE_text": "<p>Imagine walking into work—or worse, showing up to a first date—with your face literally peeling off.</p><p><br>Not exactly the \"confident, youthful\" look you're going for.</p><p><br>This is why most men try Retinol once, have a terrible experience, and never touch it again.</p>",
        "ggHvSWc0fDs_text": "<p>First, I suggested he \"just moisturize more.\" He bought some oversized bottle from Walmart. Used it for two months.<br>Nothing changed.</p><p><br>Then he saw an ad for one of those \"men's skincare systems\"—you know the ones. Sleek black bottles. Promised to make him look 10 years younger.</p><p><br>He ordered it. Did the whole routine. Morning cream, night cream, eye serum, the works.</p><p><br><strong>Six weeks later?</strong> His skin felt a little softer, maybe. But the wrinkles? The sagging neck? The tired look?</p><p><br>Still there.</p><p><br>He was frustrated. \"Maybe this is just how it is when you're almost 60,\" he said.</p>",
        "ggKcubFssZF_text": "<p>1. Retinyl Palmitate (Vitamin A)</p>",
        "ggLWhXFfn6S_text": "After 8 years of watching my divorced dad struggle to date, <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">I finally found what was holding him back...</span> and it wasn't his personality.",
        "ggLeblUhSNa_text": "<p>Week 1-2:</p>",
        "ggNeqzC4IAz_text": "<p>Then came the <strong>beef tallow</strong> phase.</p><p><br>One of his buddies from the gym told him about it. \"All natural,\" he said. \"Our grandfathers used it. None of those chemicals.\"</p><p><br>So my dad ordered a jar.</p><p><br>I'll never forget the first time I visited after he started using it.</p><p><br>He opened the door and I thought: <i>Why does it smell like a steakhouse in here?</i></p><p><br>The stuff was greasy. Like, <i>really</i> greasy. His pillowcases were stained. His face had this weird shine that didn't go away.<br><br>&nbsp;</p><p>And after three months?</p><p><br><strong>His skin actually looked worse.</strong> He'd broken out along his jawline—something that hadn't happened since he was a teenager.</p><p><br>\"I don't get it,\" he told me. \"Everyone online says this stuff is supposed to work.\"</p><p><br>That's when I started digging deeper.</p>",
        "ggP4oRCP8Jn_text": "<p>3.</p>",
        "ggPEGV--92o_text": "The Italians figured out something American brands missed.",
        "ggPFqcfb_dt_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Retinyl Palmitate</strong> in actual effective concentrations (not trace amounts)</p>",
        "ggPFqcfb_dt_childItem_1": "<p><strong>Vitamin C derived from Sicilian oranges</strong>—stabilized so it doesn't oxidize before it works</p>",
        "ggPFqcfb_dt_childItem_2": "<p><strong>Hyaluronic Acid</strong> for moisture retention and collagen protection</p>",
        "ggPFqcfb_dt_childItem_3": "<p><strong>Cold-pressed Tuscan olive oil</strong> for antioxidant protection</p>",
        "ggPFqcfb_dt_childItem_4": "<p>Anyone who's tried beef tallow, drugstore creams, or those \"men's skincare systems\" advertised on Facebook... and saw nothing change</p>",
        "ggQ2BjdEBi8_text": "<p>Option 2: Do nothing.</p>",
        "ggQiuVWWXo3_text": "That's when I found <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Omnis.</span>",
        "ggRJN3HiOMQ_text": "<p>2.</p>",
        "ggS6DpL-RTz_text": "<p>I spent hours reading dermatology journals, skincare forums, even some Italian research papers (thank God for Google Translate).</p><p><br>And what I found made me angry—not at my dad, but at the entire skincare industry.</p><p><br><strong>Here's the truth nobody tells men over 50:</strong></p><p><br>Most \"anti-aging\" products don't actually do anything to reverse aging.</p><p><br>They moisturize. They hydrate. They make your skin feel softer <i>temporarily.</i></p><p><br>But they don't address the actual reason your face is sagging, wrinkling, and looking older.</p>",
        "ggSdZqFlz3Q_text": "Then one night, after a few beers, he finally told me the truth.",
        "ggSlbG29aRP_text": "So I started helping him find a solution.",
        "ggSrH263EZZ_text": "<p>Right now, Omnis is running a U.S. launch special that makes this an easy decision.</p>",
        "ggV9J6QD8EV_childItem_0": "<p>Redness</p>",
        "ggVDObQEDyF_text": "That weekend, I went down a rabbit hole.",
        "ggVHhTTPrR7_text": "<p>Drugstore moisturizers? They just sit on the surface. They're like putting a fresh coat of paint on a house with a crumbling foundation.</p><p><br>Those \"men's skincare systems\"? Most of them are glorified moisturizers with fancy marketing. They might hydrate your skin, but they're not rebuilding the structure underneath.</p><p><br>And beef tallow?</p><p><br>Here's the thing nobody tells you about beef tallow: it's <i>occlusive.</i></p><p><br>That means it creates a barrier on TOP of your skin. It doesn't penetrate. It doesn't signal your body to do anything. It just sits there—trapping oil, clogging pores, and slowly going rancid.</p><p><br><strong>It's passive. And passive doesn't rebuild collagen.</strong></p>",
        "ggVVyyEYbd__text": "<p>It's gentle enough to actually use consistently.</p>",
        "ggVyIhHmXnA_childItem_0": "<p><strong>Less than $1 per day</strong></p>",
        "ggVyIhHmXnA_childItem_1": "<p><strong>FREE Shipping</strong></p>",
        "ggWXljIZlpy_text": "<p>Let me explain.</p><p><br>Your skin's structure—the firmness, the tightness, that \"youthful\" look—it all comes from one protein: <strong>collagen.</strong></p><p><br>Think of collagen like the scaffolding inside your skin. It's what keeps everything lifted, firm, and smooth.</p><p><br>When you're young, your body produces collagen like crazy. That's why a 25-year-old can sleep four hours, drink all weekend, and still look fresh on Monday.</p><p><br>But here's the problem:</p><p><br><strong>After 50, collagen production drops off a cliff.</strong></p><p><br>Your body makes less and less of it every year. And the collagen you do have starts breaking down faster than it's replaced.</p><p><br>The result?</p><p><br>The \"scaffolding\" collapses. Your skin loses its structure. Wrinkles form. Your jawline softens. Your neck starts to sag.</p><p><br>It's not about hydration. It's not about moisturizing.</p><p><br><strong>It's a structural problem.</strong></p>",
        "ggXBtB-MdyR_text": "<p>The way he <i>carried himself</i> was completely different.</p><p><br>That thing I'd watched for years—the shoulder drop when he caught his reflection, the collar adjustment, the defeated energy before dates—it was gone.</p><p><br>He stood straighter. Made more eye contact. Laughed easier.</p><p><br><strong>The outside finally matched the inside again.</strong></p><p><br>And other people noticed.</p><p><br>His buddy from the gym asked if he'd \"gotten work done.\" (He hadn't.)</p><p><br>A woman at his church told him he looked \"refreshed and healthy.\"</p><p><br>And then—this is the part that still makes me smile—he came back from a date one night and called me.</p><p><br>\"It went really well,\" he said. \"Like, <i>really</i> well. We're going out again Saturday.\"</p><p><br>He paused.</p><p><br>\"I felt like <i>myself</i> again. I wasn't thinking about my neck the whole time. I was just... present. Having fun.\"</p>",
        "ggXFtx4-HO2_label": "<p>&gt;&gt;&gt; TRY OMNIS RISK-FREE FOR 60 DAYS &lt;&lt;&lt;</p>",
        "ggYatpUT7jt_text": "<p>This is when things got real.</p><p><br>I visited my dad about seven weeks after he'd started using Omnis. He opened the door, and I actually did a double-take.</p><p><br>His face looked <i>firmer</i>. The sagging along his jawline—the thing he'd been hiding with high collars for years—had visibly tightened.</p><p><br>The \"turkey neck\" he'd been so self-conscious about? Still there, but noticeably reduced. The skin looked tighter, more defined.</p><p><br>He looked like himself—but the version from eight or ten years ago.</p><p><br>\"Dad,\" I said. \"You look... younger. Like, actually younger.\"</p><p><br>He grinned. \"I know. I've been staring at myself in the mirror like an idiot for the past week.\"</p>",
        "ggYnmkC4iJ-_text": "<p>It attacks the root cause, not the symptoms.</p>",
        "ggZP3avUi4F_text": "But here's what mattered more than any physical change:",
        "gg_QgPPbocW_text": "<p>Most skincare products treat your face like it just needs more moisture. They're surface-level solutions to a structural problem.</p><p><br>Omnis is different. The Retinyl Palmitate actually signals your skin cells to start producing collagen again. It's not masking the problem—it's rebuilding the foundation.</p><p><br><strong>It's the difference between putting a fresh coat of paint on a crumbling house vs. actually fixing the foundation.</strong></p>",
        "ggbOaP_42tT_text": "<p>Here's the dirty secret of anti-aging skincare:</p><p><br>The most \"powerful\" products are often so harsh that people quit using them after a week. They cause redness, peeling, irritation—and most guys would rather have wrinkles than show up to work looking like a molting snake.</p><p><br>Retinyl Palmitate delivers the collagen-building benefits of Vitamin A<i> without</i> the brutal side effects. That means you'll actually stick with it long enough to see results.</p><p><br><strong>The best product in the world doesn't work if it's sitting unused in your bathroom cabinet.</strong></p>",
        "ggc9IJ1u6l__text": "Why did this work when everything else failed?",
        "ggcOkAApa_y_text": "Getting my dad to try it wasn't easy.",
        "ggci4Yi9ZWU_text": "<p>1.</p>",
        "ggcoV4ndQOs_childItem_0": "<p>Flaking</p>",
        "ggdF8idohCo_text": "<p>While researching Retinyl Palmitate, I kept seeing references to Italian skincare formulations.</p><p><br>At first, I thought it was just marketing fluff. \"Made in Italy\" sounds fancy, but does it actually matter?</p><p><br>Turns out, it does. A lot.</p><p><br>Here's what I learned:</p><p><br><strong>Italian pharmaceutical regulations are among the strictest in the world.</strong></p><p><br>While the US FDA allows over 1,400 questionable chemicals in skincare products, Italian regulations ban most of them.</p><p>Italian products have to meet standards that American brands don't even come close to.</p><p><br>And there's something else:</p><p><br>Italian men have been taking skincare seriously for generations. It's not considered \"unmanly\" there—it's just... normal. Part of looking put-together.</p><p><br>That's why Italian labs have been quietly perfecting anti-aging formulations for decades while American brands were busy repackaging the same basic moisturizers with \"FOR MEN\" slapped on the label.</p>",
        "ggdcISJ7MsW_text": "\"Dad, you deserve to be happy again.\"",
        "ggeJWNj6-Zi_text": "<p>Week 4:</p>",
        "ggfCpDqx-r1_text": "Then I discovered something interesting about Italy.",
        "ggfQ9IYU1eD_text": "And that's exactly why most skincare products fail men over 50.",
        "ggg1EChFWS8_text": "<p><strong>\"The Italian Gentleman Blueprint: How to Be Irresistible to Women (Including Your Wife)\"</strong></p>",
        "ggg6GvHimGc_text": "<p>$24.99/Bottle</p>",
        "ggiXvGNpWxt_text": "<p>4.8 out of 5 | 7,405+ Reviews</p>",
        "ggk-suBPzhI_text": "<p>Week 6-8:</p>",
        "ggk3Tsu6v0h_text": "Let me be blunt about what DOESN'T work:",
        "ggkjolkO4CW_text": "<p>Close this page. Go back to what you were doing.</p><p><br>Your skin will continue doing what it's been doing—producing less collagen every year, losing more structure, sagging a little more.</p><p><br>That's not a scare tactic. It's just biology. After 50, this process doesn't reverse itself. It doesn't plateau. It continues.</p><p><br>The guy in the mirror next year will look older than the guy in the mirror today.</p><p><br><strong>Risk: None (today) Guaranteed outcome: Continued decline</strong></p>",
        "ggksszJQ0ss_text": "<p>It's not just about <i>one</i> miracle ingredient.</p><p><br>It's about how ingredients <i>work</i> together.</p><p><br>The most effective Italian formulations combine three key elements:</p>",
        "ggljhTNei8L_text": "<p>My dad is not a \"skincare routine\" guy. He was never going to do a 5-step morning ritual with serums and toners and eye creams.</p><p><br>Omnis is one step. At night. Takes about 30 seconds.</p><p><br>Brush your teeth, apply the cream, go to bed. That's it.</p><p><br>Your skin does most of its repair work while you sleep anyway. Omnis just gives it the raw materials it needs to rebuild.</p><p><br><strong>Simple enough that even the most routine-averse guy will actually do it.</strong></p>",
        "gglocQE8MOC_text": "The real problem? After 50, your skin stops building itself.",
        "ggmR7qlD9g7_text": "<p>He needed something that would actually <i>restart</i> his skin's collagen production.</p><p><br>Something that would penetrate below the surface and tell his skin cells: \"Hey, wake up. Start building again.\"</p><p><br>And that's when I found the research on <strong>Retinyl Palmitate.</strong></p>",
        "ggmzoBjaO9G_text": "Omnis Uomo Anti-Aging Night Cream",
        "ggoNpSaz-Ye_text": "<p>\"Huh. This actually feels different.\"</p>",
        "ggoYNHah_jc_text": "U.S. Launch Special: <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Up to</span> <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">64%OFF</span>",
        "ggotxhPnviL_text": "<p>Here's my promise to you:</p><p><br>Try Omnis for 60 days. Use it every night. Give it the full 8 weeks to work.</p><p><br>If you don't look in the mirror and see a visible difference—firmer skin, softer wrinkles, a more defined jawline—we'll refund every penny.</p><p><br>No hoops. No hassle. No \"restocking fees.\" Just email the support team and you'll get your money back.</p><p><br><strong>You're not risking $69.99 today. You're risking $0.</strong></p><p><br>The only thing you're risking is the possibility of looking and feeling like yourself again.</p><p><br>That's a bet worth taking.</p>",
        "ggp4c0exzuk_text": "<p>How an Italian night cream helped my 59-year-old father look \"10 years younger\" in 8 weeks—and finally feel confident enough to put himself back out there.</p>",
        "ggqqJi7itZz_text": "<p>This is the \"protective layer.\" It holds moisture deep in the skin (preventing that dry, weathered look) and—this is the important part—it blocks the enzymes that break down collagen. So while you're building new collagen, you're also protecting what's already there..</p>",
        "ggr9ky8RUP-_text": "The <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">\"Look in the Mirror\"</span> Guarantee",
        "ggt0wfkqYCt_text": "<p>The Italians call this combination approach <i>\"costruzione e protezione\"</i>—building and protecting.</p><p><br><strong>You're not just adding moisture to the surface. You're rebuilding the structure underneath while defending it from further breakdown.</strong></p>",
        "ggtQ1BwUsTR_text": "What my dad needed wasn't a moisturizer.",
        "ggv1Z9WXcSC_text": "<p>\"I've already wasted money on three different products,\" he said. \"I'm done being a sucker.\"</p><p><br>I understood his skepticism. He'd been burned before—literally, in the case of a drugstore Retinol that left his face raw for a week.</p><p><br>But I showed him the research. Explained the difference between harsh Retinol and gentle Retinyl Palmitate. Told him about the Italian pharmaceutical standards.</p><p><br>And then I mentioned the 60-day money-back guarantee.</p><p><br>\"Look,\" I said, \"if it doesn't work, you get your money back. You've got nothing to lose except eight weeks.\"</p><p><br>He agreed to try it. Reluctantly.</p>",
        "ggv1tG1_tI7_text": "<p>3. Hyaluronic Acid</p>",
        "ggvC6XpiOFk_text": "<p>The first thing my dad noticed was the texture.</p><p><br>\"It's not greasy,\" he said, almost surprised. \"It actually absorbs. I don't feel like I'm wearing a mask to bed.\"</p><p><br>After about a week, he mentioned his skin felt smoother. More hydrated. Not tight and dry like it usually felt in the morning.</p><p><br>\"People at work asked if I'd gotten more sleep,\" he told me. \"I haven't. But I guess I look like I have.\"</p><p><br>It wasn't dramatic yet. But something was shifting.</p>",
        "ggvmBCDOAvy_text": "<p>— $40 value</p>",
        "ggvnJSPygQp_text": "<p>That's six full months of supply—enough to complete the entire transformation timeline.</p>",
        "ggwOYinMj_1_text": "<p>Option 1: Give Omnis a real shot.</p>",
        "ggwTFaBiaDS_text": "Retinyl Palmitate: The \"Gentleman's Retinol\"",
        "ggwY3K1iKUH_text": "<p>\"You want to know what it is?\" he said, not quite looking at me. \"It's my neck.\"</p><p><br>He pulled his collar down slightly.</p><p><br>\"I look in the mirror and I see this... this <i>turkey neck</i>... and all I can think is, 'She's going to see this across the table. She's going to see how old I've gotten.'\"</p><p><br>He wasn't wrong that things had changed. The skin under his jaw had loosened. There were lines on his face that hadn't been there five years ago. He looked <i>tired</i>—even when he wasn't.</p><p><br>But here's what broke my heart:</p><p><br><strong>My dad is one of the sharpest, funniest, most generous men I know.</strong> He'd be an incredible partner for someone. But he couldn't see past what he saw in that mirror.</p><p><br>And I realized: it wasn't vanity. It was that the outside didn't match the inside anymore.</p><p><br>He still felt 45 inside. Energetic. Curious. Plenty of life left to live.</p><p><br>But his face was telling a different story.</p>",
        "ggwrbWPnMzF_text": "<p>Collagen is fragile when it's first produced. Vitamin C acts like \"reinforcement\"—it makes the new collagen fibers stronger and more resilient. Sicilian oranges have some of the highest concentrations of stable Vitamin C in the world.</p>",
        "ggwyjogliVI_text": "<p>After watching my dad's transformation, I kept coming back to this question.</p><p><br>He'd tried drugstore moisturizers. Nothing.</p><p><br>He'd tried those \"men's skincare systems\" with the sleek marketing. Nothing.</p><p><br>He'd tried beef tallow—the \"all-natural ancestral\" solution. Made things worse.</p><p><br>So why did Omnis actually deliver results?</p><p><br>I think it comes down to three things:</p>",
        "ggyk0H4folA_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\"><strong>FREE Ebook Included:</strong></span></p>",
        "ggyq-p3Fywh_text": "<p>\"Holy sh*t.\"</p>",
        "ggyv7g3mW0l_text": "<p>The \"signal\" that tells your skin cells to start producing collagen again. The gentle version that won't leave you red and peeling.</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_0": "<p>Men over 50 who feel like they've become \"invisible\" to women—like they're looked through instead of looked at</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_1": "<p>Divorced or widowed guys who want to get back out there but feel self-conscious every time they look in the mirror</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_2": "<p>Men who look in photos and think \"when did I start looking like my father?\"</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_3": "<p>Guys whose face doesn't match how young they still feel inside</p>",
        "ggz0rpV5FJT_childItem_4": "<p>Anyone who&#039;s tried beef tallow, drugstore creams, or those \"men&#039;s skincare systems\" advertised on Facebook... and saw nothing change</p>"
      },
